# Reports

---

## Auth-R1 User Login & RBAC Integration Report
**Status:** verified
**Module:** auth

---

## Executive Summary

Successfully integrated the existing `backend/src/rbac/` module into the main Axum application and implemented complete Vue 3 authentication UI. The RBAC backend (SQLite-backed user/role/permission storage, JWT auth via `jsonwebtoken`, bcrypt password hashing, Axum middleware) was fully wired into `main.rs` with proper route layering. Frontend components (`useAuth.ts` composable, `LoginView.vue`, auth guard in `App.vue`) were implemented with JWT token lifecycle management and automatic `Authorization: Bearer` header injection.

## Implementation Summary

### Backend Integration ✅

**`backend/src/main.rs`**
- Imported `RbacState`, `rbac_api_routes`, `auth_middleware`, `RbacMiddlewareState`
- Implemented `load_or_create_jwt_secret()` — generates 64-byte hex secret persisted to `{data_dir}/autoforge/jwt_secret.txt`
- Added `health_handler()` at `GET /api/health` returning 200 OK
- Split routing into public (health + auth routes) and protected (forge routes) layers
- Applied `auth_middleware` layer to protected router — validates JWT, injects `AuthUser` into extensions
- Registered `POST /api/auth/login` and `POST /api/auth/register` routes
- Default admin user (admin/admin) seeded on first run via `RbacState::new()`

**`backend/src/rbac/api.rs`**
- Added `register()` handler — validates username/password (≥4 chars), checks uniqueness, hashes with bcrypt, creates user with "editor" role, returns JWT

### Frontend Implementation ✅

**`frontend/src/composables/useAuth.ts` (NEW)**
- Singleton auth state: `_token`, `_user`, `_loading`, `_error` refs
- `login(username, password)` — POST to `/api/auth/login`, stores JWT to localStorage
- `register(username, password)` — POST to `/api/auth/register`, stores JWT
- `logout()` — clears token and user, redirects to login
- `me()` — fetches current user from `/api/auth/me`, validates token
- `validateStoredToken()` — validates stored JWT on app mount
- `authFetch(url, options)` — wrapper adding `Authorization: Bearer` header, clears auth on 401
- Computed: `isAuthenticated`, `isAdmin`

**`frontend/src/views/LoginView.vue` (NEW)**
- Login/register form with username + password inputs
- Toggle between modes (login vs register)
- Error display with i18n via `t()`
- Flame icon branding
- Emits `auth-success` event on successful login/register

**`frontend/src/App.vue`**
- Auth guard: `v-if="!isAuthenticated"` shows LoginView
- On mount: calls `validateStoredToken()`
- User menu in `.rail-footer`: avatar circle + logout button
- Logout clears auth state and returns to LoginView

**All frontend composables (7 files)**
- Replaced `fetch(` with `authFetch(` from `useAuth.ts`
- Files: `useForge.ts`, `useRelay.ts`, `useSpecs.ts`, `useWiki.ts`, `useApiSources.ts`, `useAgentConfigs.ts`, `useProject.ts`

**i18n locales**
- Added keys to `en.json` and `zh.json`: `auth.username`, `auth.password`, `auth.login`, `auth.register`, `auth.logout`, etc.

